title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.1: COMMUNITY BEHAVIOUR CHANGE - HIV-AIDS AND CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: Output 3.1: Children, parents, caregivers and communities in target counties, urban informal settlements and refugee settings have knowledge and adopt desirable practices to prevent and respond to HIV/AIDS, violence, abuse and exploitation of girls and boys, and have improved service-seeking behaviour, which contributes to Access To Justice, Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Hiv Prevention. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 3 - Children and adolescents are increasingly protected from exposure to HIV and AIDS, violence, abuse, exploitation and harmful cultural practices, and benefit from increased access to prevention, care, treatment, support, justice and other services needed to ensure their physical, mental and social wellbeing.

description.narrative: In total, 86,346 people including girls, boys, parents and community members participated in communication interventions on addressing violence against children, exceeding the 2019 target. All 47 counties are now reporting on age- and sex-disaggregated data on HIV testing and counselling among adolescents. Programmes on integrated life skills and awareness creation on the drivers that increase child and adolescent vulnerability to VAC, unintended pregnancies and HIV were implemented in seven counties. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
